sys_hub_action_type_definition.description:
Creates an instance template from instance.

Inputs:

  • Project ID - Unique ID of the project.
  • Zone - Name of the zone.
  • Instance - Name of the instance.
  • Name - Name of the instance template.
  • Description - Description of this resource.
  • Disk Configs - Disk configs an object containing Device Name, Image, Instantiate From, Auto Delete.

Outputs:

  • Instance Template - Instance template is an object containing Name, ID, Operation Type, Target Link, Target ID, Status, User, Progress, Insert Time, Start Time, Self-Link, Kind.
  • Status - If the request is executed successfully, Status is set to “Success”. If there is a failure in Google Compute Engine, Status is set to “Error".
  • Error Message - Reason for error. Populated only when an error occurs.

Error Messages:

  • Instance template is already exist.
  • Invalid Project ID has been passed.
  • Invalid image URL has been passed.
  • Invalid subnetwork has been passed.
  • Invalid network interface values has been passed.
  • Device name specified in disk instantiation config not found in requested source instance.
  • Invalid authorization header. The access token you're using is either expired or invalid.

To use this action, a corresponding Google Compute Engine connection and credential must be created and associated with the Google Compute Engine Connection & Credential alias. Learn More

Note: Requires a subscription for production use. Read More.
